        {
          "AID": "3a-iii-2",
          "prettyAID": "b",
          "answer": "no",
          "description": "Section 504’s requirements are applicable to all learning environments, including for remote learning and any formats used during all stages of reopening.When materials are not available in an accessible format, such as an inaccessible scanned PDF file of a short article that does not contain numerous charts and tables, educators could meet their legal obligations by providing students with disabilities with equally effective alternate access to the materials or services provided to other students such as an audio recording of the text of the scanned PDF document. However, many disability-related modifications and services might be provided effectively in remote learning. These could include, for example, extensions of time for assignments, videos with accurate captioning or embedded sign language interpreting, accessible reading materials, and many speech or language services through video conferencing.",
          "resources": [],
          "nextQID": "3a-iv"
        }
